Title: Terrai SPF50 Multiprotect - SPF 50 PA+++
Description: Exposure of skin to rays from the sun is unavoidable. Sunlight energizes and provides vitamin D, but it can also deliver damaging ultraviolet (UV) radiation. Long-term exposure to UV rays from the sun can lead to a number of skin conditions ranging from wrinkles, aging and discoloration to skin cancer. Sunscreens are rated by their sun protection factor, or SPF, which refers to the ability of the product to protect the skin from harmful UVB (skin burning) rays and PA system, which shows the ability of the product to protect the skin against harmful UV A (skin aging) rays. TERRAI sunscreens providesuperior broad-spectrum protection from both UVA and UVB rays. This PA ranking is done on a +, ++, and +++ scale, with the higher amount of pluses indicating the higher the protection. The SPF rating is number based. Higher the SPF number, the more UVB rays are blocked. Studies show that SPF 15 sunscreen blocks appx. 93% of UVB radiation, while an SPF 30 sunscreen blocks nearly 97% and an SPF 50 blocks an estimated 98%.To protect your skin, we recommend you choose products with a minimum SPF rating of 30 and a maximum SPF rating of 50.Zinc Oxide used in our formulation is an effectivenatural sunscreen agent, an anti-irritant and a skin protector. Our barely there, tinted mineral formula evens out minor imperfections on the face and bodyUse: Liberally apply the product to all areas that will be exposed to the sun. Make For maximum protection we advise that you apply our product 15 minutes before going out in the sun, to allow the skin to absorb the protective ingredients.For continued protection, reapply TERRAI Sunscreen every 2-4 hours or anytime you get out of the water and/or towel off.Use sun protection all year long, whether the weather is sunny or cloudy.For external use only •Waterproof, No Sweat Formula•Non-greasy•Paraben free•PABA-free, oil free, does not clog pores•Light feel formula•SPF 30 (UV B) PA++ (UV A) :: SPF 50 (UV B) PA+++ (UV A)
